name: **Cone Island South**
description: Cone Island South F723-388 A double island 2km SE of Danish Cellar and separated from Ooghran Point by a narrow channel that in itself merits a trip for those exploring the coast on the W side of Broadhaven Bay. Both islands are steep and precipitous and separated by an attractive channel. The larger more NE island has a small sea arch on its E side. Landing is possible on the larger more NE island on to rock shelves both at the SW corner and in the channel between the islands. No water and no camping. Breeding Fulmars, GBB & Herring Gulls.
